Sherlock
Find usernames across social networks

Social Engineering
Description
Sherlock hunts down social media accounts by username across 300+ social networks. Essential OSINT tool for finding a person's online presence.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which sherlock
Install command:

pip install sherlock-project
Basic Syntax
sherlock <username>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
sherlock username

Search all sites	Find user profiles	
sherlock username --timeout 10

With timeout	Faster results	
sherlock user1 user2 user3

Multiple users	Batch search	
sherlock username --output results.txt

Save results	Export findings	
sherlock username --print-found

Only found accounts	Clean output	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Choose target username
2
Run sherlock
3
Review found profiles
4
Visit profiles for verification
5
Document findings
Understanding the Output
Lists social media URLs where the username was found.

Important Warnings
•
Respect privacy laws
•
Verify findings manually
•
Use for authorized investigations only
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
